{
  "texts": [
    "In this section, we provide relevant background on transformer architectures and elaborate on relevant fine-tuning methods proposed for transformers.",
    "A. Computation KernelThe transformer architecture is composed of multiple sequential layers of encoder/decoder blocks.",
    "Each of these blocks consists of two major functional modules: multi-head attention (MHA) and feed-forward (FF) network [1].",
    "The MHA module employs multiple attention heads with each head computing attention scores [1].",
    "Conversely, the FF module is a fully connected network consisting of two linear layers designed to process the data sequentially [1]."
  ]
}